info.title: Last Night I Had The Strangest Dream

lines.text: i dreamed the world had all agreed
to put an end to war
the room was filled with men
and when the papers all were signed
they all joined hands and-bowed their heads

paragraphs.text: last night i had the strangest dream i ever dreamed before i dreamed the world had all agreed to put an end to war i dreamed i saw a mighty room the room was filled with men and the paper they were signin' said they'd never fight again

and when the papers all were signed and a million copies made they all joined hands and-bowed their heads and grateful prayers were prayed and the people in the street below were dancing round and round and guns and swords and uniforms were scattered all around
